<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.199259>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Semi – schematic line drawings of Asetadiptacus acarubri n. sp.: A. Lateral posterior region of female; B. Lateral opisthosomal annuli; C. Lateral anterior region of female; D. Leg I; E. Empodium; F. Internal female genitalia; G. Male genital shield; H. Prodorsal shield; I. Coxigenital region of female. Scale bar: 27 µm for A & C; 20 µm for F, G, H & I; 13 µm for B & D; 4 µm for E." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/199259/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.199260>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Digital micrographs of the prodorsal shield and coxigenital region. Asetadiptacus acarubri n. sp. Mature protogyne female. Scale bar: 20 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/199260/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.199255>
